<doc id="336350" wikidata="Q2359276" url="?curid=336350" title="Dixieland Jubilee Records">
<text>Dixieland Jubilee Records was an American record label during the 1950s that released Dixieland jazz. The label&#x27;s roster included Teddy Buckner, Kid Ory, and Wild Bill Davison. Dixieland Jubilee was owned by Frank Bull and Gene Norman and run by Norman, who owned GNP Crescendo.

